WEBVTT

00:02.698 --> 00:04.134
ADULT ADAM: Growing up,
there was nothing better
than the school field trip,

00:04.221 --> 00:07.355
that rare opportunity to skip your classes and head out on an adventure.

00:07.442 --> 00:09.661
Yep, field trips
were the best.

00:09.748 --> 00:11.794
Boofaloo, come play I Spy!

00:11.881 --> 00:14.275
Unfortunately, my smother
was always there.

00:14.362 --> 00:16.103
I spy
a handsome schmendrick

00:16.190 --> 00:18.931
I'm gonna squeeze all the way
to the Liberty Bell!

00:19.019 --> 00:22.413
And this time, our trip
was low on education
and high on fun!

00:22.500 --> 00:24.937
We were going to Hersheypark!

00:25.025 --> 00:27.592
I can't believe we're
finally going to Hershey,
Pennsylvania!

00:27.679 --> 00:29.507
I hear the air there
smells like chocolate!

00:29.594 --> 00:32.162
I hear the streets
are paved with nougat!

00:32.249 --> 00:34.469
When you're over
five feet tall, you're
considered a Twizzler.

00:34.556 --> 00:36.210
It means we can go
on any ride.

00:36.297 --> 00:37.907
Well, we can go
on any ride.

00:37.994 --> 00:39.909
Your mom always chaperones

00:39.996 --> 00:41.128
and there's no way
she'll let you loose

00:41.215 --> 00:42.607
into Chocolate Town USA
without her.

00:42.694 --> 00:43.913
It's your own fault,
dude.

00:44.000 --> 00:45.132
The rest of us
forced our parents

00:45.219 --> 00:46.655
to stop chaperoning
years ago.

00:46.742 --> 00:48.309
Yeah, all you got to do
is lay down

00:48.396 --> 00:49.832
some clear boundaries
with your mom.

00:49.919 --> 00:53.053
Oh. Uh, oh,
is that all I got to do? Huh.

00:53.140 --> 00:56.491
I didn't know
it was so easy!

00:56.578 --> 00:58.536
Thank you, Clueless Chad!

00:58.623 --> 01:00.147
You get mean when
it involves your mom.

01:00.234 --> 01:02.018
My mom needs
these field trips.

01:02.105 --> 01:04.499
It's the only
school-sanctioned opportunity
she has left

01:04.586 --> 01:06.066
to painfully insert herself
into my life.

01:06.153 --> 01:08.372
Well, I told my mom,
"No more!

01:08.459 --> 01:11.593
"Dave Kim is a grown-up
who doesn't need his mommy
on some field trip!

01:11.680 --> 01:13.725
"Now sign my permission slip
and lay out my clothes!"

01:13.812 --> 01:15.162
That would never work
for Adam.

01:15.249 --> 01:17.599
All I know is that
this ends today!

01:17.686 --> 01:19.949
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYS]
I've waited my whole life to
eat eight pounds of chocolate,

01:20.036 --> 01:23.039
then ride
crazy roller coasters
till I hork.

01:23.126 --> 01:25.955
I'm an adult man now
and shall not be controlled.

01:26.042 --> 01:30.046
It's time I finally face
Beverly Goldberg
once and for all!

01:30.133 --> 01:31.874
[MUSIC ENDS]

01:31.961 --> 01:33.658
You're gonna lie to her,
aren't you?Right to her face!

01:33.745 --> 01:35.051
What?

01:35.138 --> 01:37.619
Hersheypark has been closed
and our trip is off!

01:37.706 --> 01:40.274
Why are they trying to ruin
our precious time together?

01:40.361 --> 01:41.579
'Cause of
the Chocolate Wars.

01:41.666 --> 01:43.015
You didn't hear about it
on the news?

01:43.103 --> 01:44.669
No,
I don't watch the news.

01:44.756 --> 01:46.758
It aggravates your father till
he throws his shoe at the TV.

01:46.845 --> 01:49.500
It's those Fudge Barons
at Nestle Megacorp.

01:49.587 --> 01:51.546
They declared an all-out war
on Mr. Goodbar

01:51.633 --> 01:53.374
so they shut down
the amusement park.

01:53.461 --> 01:55.202
Screw those
Chocolate War-Mongers!

01:55.289 --> 01:58.727
I just made a fresh batch
of Oooey Gooey Fudgy Chewies.

01:58.814 --> 02:00.511
[CHUCKLES]
These always cheer you up.

02:02.078 --> 02:03.471
Wow.
He's good.

02:04.907 --> 02:06.213
Maybe the best.

02:08.519 --> 02:10.652
♪ I'm twisted up inside

02:10.739 --> 02:13.394
♪ But nonetheless
I feel the need to say

02:16.179 --> 02:18.094
♪ I don't know the future

02:18.181 --> 02:20.923
♪ But the past keeps getting
clearer every day ♪

02:21.010 --> 02:23.534
ADULT ADAM:
It was October 17th,
1980-something,

02:23.621 --> 02:26.798
the night of the annual
Career Fair
at William Penn Academy...

02:26.885 --> 02:29.323
Hello, everyone,
and welcome to
Career Night.

02:29.410 --> 02:31.325
[COUGHS]
No-one-cares![LAUGHTER]

02:31.412 --> 02:34.066
Okay, well, the joke's on you,
mysterious cougher.

02:34.154 --> 02:35.851
The path
that you choose tonight

02:35.938 --> 02:38.332
will determine
the rest of your lives.

02:38.419 --> 02:41.073
Rest of our lives? Oh, man.
That sounds pretty permanent.

02:41.161 --> 02:42.771
Lucky for you, you have

02:42.858 --> 02:44.947
your old man's noble
profession of ophthalmology

02:45.034 --> 02:46.078
pre-selected for you.

02:46.166 --> 02:48.037
You're so lucky!

02:48.124 --> 02:50.822
I have tons of questions
about doctoring,
Mister Dr. Geoff's Dad!

02:50.909 --> 02:53.695
Okay, I see how passionate
you are about medicine.

02:53.782 --> 02:55.784
Come by the office and see
for yourself what I do.

02:55.871 --> 02:57.916
I call eyeball holder
when you do a head transplant!

02:58.003 --> 02:59.570
Boom!

02:59.657 --> 03:01.050
I know that's not
real science,

03:01.137 --> 03:02.225
but I'm still
gonna take a walk.

03:04.096 --> 03:05.359
How's it going?

03:05.446 --> 03:07.187
Well, my "rock star" booth
is an obvious sham,

03:07.274 --> 03:09.885
but I'm broke
and they got free food,
so goin' good. You?

03:09.972 --> 03:12.366
Well, my dad's pushing me into
the eyeball game, so, gross?

03:12.453 --> 03:14.324
Dude, you're at
a career night.

03:14.411 --> 03:16.370
If eye doctoring
skeeves you out so much,
then go find another job.

03:16.457 --> 03:17.675
What? No.

03:17.762 --> 03:20.591
I... I love the human eye,
all squishy with its veins

03:20.678 --> 03:22.289
and mysterious,
disgusting rings.

03:22.376 --> 03:23.812
Are you gonna hurl?
I might.

03:23.899 --> 03:25.988
Hey, you!
Me?

03:26.075 --> 03:28.991
Yeah, you! The kid who ate
my corn on the cob. Come here!

03:29.078 --> 03:30.906
That was one time
two years ago.

03:30.993 --> 03:32.168
How is that the only thing
he remembers about me?

03:32.255 --> 03:33.430
He really likes his corn.

03:33.517 --> 03:35.476
Why is your dad
even at a school event?

03:35.563 --> 03:37.782
He finds a few idiots
to move heavy crap for free

03:37.869 --> 03:39.001
and then
he calls them interns.

03:39.088 --> 03:40.611
[SIGHS]

03:40.698 --> 03:43.048
Hey, niblets. How would
you feel about interning

03:43.135 --> 03:46.008
in the exciting world of new
and recycled furniture sales?

03:46.095 --> 03:47.401
Um, maybe, I guess.

03:47.488 --> 03:48.837
You're hired.

03:48.924 --> 03:50.404
And by hired, I don't mean
I'm actually paying you.

03:50.491 --> 03:52.014
Geoff!
Get back to the booth!

03:52.101 --> 03:54.016
This young man's being
very disrespectful

03:54.103 --> 03:55.800
to my anatomical
eye models.

03:55.887 --> 03:58.499
Check it out, I'm putting
a giant eye in my pants!

04:00.152 --> 04:02.720
Chaperones, we'll meet here
at 8:00 a.m. sharp

04:02.807 --> 04:05.636
to hit the Hershey Highway
before it clogs up.

04:05.723 --> 04:07.029
[QUIET LAUGHTER]
All right, grow up.

04:07.116 --> 04:08.944
What the hell,
ladies and Vinny?

04:09.031 --> 04:10.162
What happened to
our PTA meeting?

04:10.250 --> 04:11.903
We got bumped.

04:11.990 --> 04:14.341
Mellor's talking to all
the field trip chaperones.

04:14.428 --> 04:17.344
Field trip? Doesn't he know
the amusement park
is closed indefinitely?

04:17.431 --> 04:18.867
What?
The park is closed?

04:18.954 --> 04:21.826
Hello? Nestle pulled out
of the Cocoa Accords.

04:21.913 --> 04:23.393
There's been
a travel advisory.

04:23.480 --> 04:25.787
All non-essential personnel
must steer clear.

04:25.874 --> 04:29.225
Uh, Beverly? None of
your insane words are true.

04:29.312 --> 04:31.009
But that's not possible.

04:31.096 --> 04:33.969
Adam swore to me that Reese's
was literally blown to pieces.

04:34.056 --> 04:37.407
Exactly. You're the
last person in the world
he wants on a field trip.

04:37.494 --> 04:38.713
But chaperoning
is the one thing

04:38.800 --> 04:40.802
I'm still allowed
to be a part of!

04:40.889 --> 04:42.717
Just feel lucky you made it
to 10th grade, Bev.

04:42.804 --> 04:44.719
Jackie cut me off
in 8th grade.

04:44.806 --> 04:45.981
Independence Hall.

04:46.068 --> 04:47.243
6th grade, Freedom Trail.

04:47.330 --> 04:49.593
5th grade.
Ben Franklin Museum.

04:49.680 --> 04:51.203
Dave Kim told me to
[VOICE BREAKING]
go fly a kite.

04:51.291 --> 04:54.076
For me it was 3rd grade.
My Emmy is garbage.

04:54.163 --> 04:56.121
But those field trips
are my only window

04:56.208 --> 04:58.080
into Adam's
day-to-day life.

04:58.167 --> 05:00.952
Without them,
how am I supposed to know
how he's doing in school?

05:01.039 --> 05:03.128
You could just ask him
when he comes home?

05:03.215 --> 05:06.697
Please. Whenever I ask about
his day, all I get is "Muh."

05:06.784 --> 05:08.438
Aw, you get
actual sounds?

05:08.525 --> 05:10.788
I just get
soul-destroying silence.

05:10.875 --> 05:14.139
Well, you may all be fine
with a frosty cold "muh"
at the end of your day,

05:14.226 --> 05:16.446
but not Beverly Goldberg.

05:16.533 --> 05:18.753
Coach, put me down
for chaperone.

05:18.840 --> 05:21.451
But your son made it clear
you're the worst
and you can't go.

05:21.538 --> 05:25.847
Lucky for me, I have a way
to get Adam to say yes
to whatever I want.

05:25.934 --> 05:28.240
ADULT ADAM:
It was true. She really did.

05:28.328 --> 05:30.330
Before parents
could guilt their kids
through texts or e-mails,

05:30.417 --> 05:33.768
my mom used the Guilt Letter.

05:33.855 --> 05:36.858
These passive-aggressive
tirades of manipulation
were a true art form.

05:36.945 --> 05:39.948
[DRAMATIC NOTES PLAY]

05:40.035 --> 05:41.732
And if her words
didn't get to you,

05:41.819 --> 05:43.430
the mom tears on the letter
sure would.

05:44.648 --> 05:45.432
Balls!

05:46.346 --> 05:48.435
♪♪

05:48.522 --> 05:50.001
I got to admit it, Cobby,

05:50.088 --> 05:52.439
you're the best pretend intern
I've had yet.

05:52.526 --> 05:54.397
I didn't realize how cool
it was to run a business.

05:54.484 --> 05:56.878
What do you mean?
Your dad runs a whole
eye doctoring business.

05:56.965 --> 05:58.749
Yeah, but in our business,
if we mess up,

05:58.836 --> 06:00.882
people will never
see their children again.

06:00.969 --> 06:02.666
The worst I can do around here
is stain a loveseat.

06:02.753 --> 06:04.581
Look, I don't want
to get involved

06:04.668 --> 06:05.974
between you
and your old man,

06:06.061 --> 06:07.671
mostly 'cause I don't care,

06:07.758 --> 06:10.718
but if eyes freak you out,
I wouldn't do eyes.

06:10.805 --> 06:12.937
What would I do with my life
if not eye doctoring?

06:13.024 --> 06:15.984
I'm not involved,
but do what makes you happy

06:16.071 --> 06:18.203
instead of being
such a pushover
all the time.

06:18.290 --> 06:20.423
I know you're not involved,
but, oh, man,

06:20.510 --> 06:22.120
I'm suddenly rethinking
my entire future!

06:22.207 --> 06:23.687
Well, why don't you
think about it while you bring

06:23.774 --> 06:24.993
that heavy-ass end table
to the back room?

06:26.081 --> 06:27.517
[CHIMES RING]

06:27.604 --> 06:29.214
Okay, you can
take your son back now!

06:29.301 --> 06:30.955
He's been shadowing me
all day.

06:31.042 --> 06:32.870
In fact,
I learned so much,

06:32.957 --> 06:34.611
Dr. Lou said I don't have to
go back tomorrow!

06:34.698 --> 06:36.744
Or ever again.
We'll play it by ear.

06:36.831 --> 06:38.615
Oh, crap, it's my dad.
Hello, Father.

06:38.702 --> 06:39.573
Geoffrey?
Where were you all day?

06:39.660 --> 06:40.791
There was an outbreak
of pink eye.

06:40.878 --> 06:41.923
So gunky, bro.

06:42.010 --> 06:43.620
Ew, bummed
I missed it. Ew.

06:43.707 --> 06:47.102
Uh, I was learning about
furniture here.

06:47.189 --> 06:49.974
You spent the day learning
another man's trade?

06:50.061 --> 06:51.585
Murray, how could you
betray me like this?

06:51.672 --> 06:53.282
No betrayal.
I'm not involved.

06:53.369 --> 06:54.936
Son, the only business
you need to know

06:55.023 --> 06:56.590
is the one
I'm handing to you.

06:56.677 --> 06:59.375
But Mr. G got me thinking that
maybe I don't want it, right?

06:59.462 --> 07:01.203
Not involved.

07:01.290 --> 07:03.031
Don't want it?
What's he talking
about, Murray?

07:03.118 --> 07:05.816
Look, all I know is this
wonderful mentor of mine...Notvolved!

07:05.903 --> 07:07.296
...told me to stick up
for myself.

07:07.383 --> 07:09.167
So, I'll just say it.
Not involved!

07:09.254 --> 07:12.214
I hereby reject
all professional doctoring
and modern medicine.

07:12.301 --> 07:13.650
So what are you gonna do
with your life?

07:13.737 --> 07:15.435
This? Furniture sales?

07:15.522 --> 07:16.784
Notvolved!

07:16.871 --> 07:18.960
I'd rather do anything
than eyes!

07:19.047 --> 07:21.049
Maybe I'll do computers
or fitness

07:21.136 --> 07:23.791
or maybe I'll just start
my own food delivery service!

07:23.878 --> 07:25.488
He wants to do
food delivery

07:25.575 --> 07:27.229
instead of helping
people see, Murray?

07:27.316 --> 07:29.840
Notvolved! Come on!

07:29.927 --> 07:31.973
ADULT ADAM: Yep, all my dad
wanted was to stay out
of Geoff's business.

07:32.060 --> 07:35.150
Meanwhile, my mom had
successfully guilted her way
back into mine.

07:35.237 --> 07:36.891
Hi, Mama.

07:36.978 --> 07:39.720
I just wanted to
say sorry and all.

07:39.807 --> 07:41.939
For?
For being a bad son

07:42.026 --> 07:45.552
and not appreciating
the time you spent
baking me in your belly.

07:45.639 --> 07:47.771
And how will you
make it up to me?

07:47.858 --> 07:49.207
Maybe you can chaperone
the field trip?

07:49.294 --> 07:51.993
I'll have to move some things
around, but I'll be there.

07:52.080 --> 07:54.038
Now go. Be a boy!

07:54.125 --> 07:56.345
My mom had guilted me
into submission,

07:56.432 --> 07:58.521
but even better,
she impressed her friends.

07:58.608 --> 08:00.610
I don't understand.
How?

08:00.697 --> 08:02.003
I can't tell you that.

08:02.090 --> 08:04.005
So you get to participate
in Adam's school life

08:04.092 --> 08:05.397
as he frolics about
with friends

08:05.485 --> 08:07.269
while the rest of us
stay home and suck it?

08:07.356 --> 08:08.836
I'm sorry, Dave Kim's mom.

08:08.923 --> 08:11.142
I just can't risk something
this huge getting out.

08:11.229 --> 08:12.535
I give you my word
as a parent

08:12.622 --> 08:14.711
and as an esteemed
kindergarten teacher.

08:14.798 --> 08:16.321
I will say nothing.

08:16.408 --> 08:17.453
Same here!
Ditto.

08:17.540 --> 08:18.933
Agreed.

08:19.020 --> 08:21.239
Meet me in my basement
at 1600 hours.

08:21.326 --> 08:23.503
Take separate cars,
don't let anyone follow you,

08:23.590 --> 08:25.722
and do not park
on our street.

08:25.809 --> 08:28.725
You're about to learn
Beverly Goldberg's
biggest secret.

08:28.812 --> 08:30.248
[QUIET LAUGHTER]

08:30.335 --> 08:32.512
Hey! Why you guys looking
all shady right now?

08:32.599 --> 08:33.600
Nothing!
No big secrets here.

08:33.687 --> 08:34.383
We're normal.
All good.

08:36.037 --> 08:36.864
Carry on.

08:40.084 --> 08:41.999
ADULT ADAM: The time
had come for my mom

08:42.086 --> 08:45.046
to teach her fellow parents
a master class
in the art of manipulation.

08:45.133 --> 08:48.136
What I'm about to show you
is the most lethal

08:48.223 --> 08:51.313
and powerful weapon
in a yenta's arsenal.

08:51.400 --> 08:53.054
The guilt letter.

08:53.141 --> 08:56.274
You wrote eight pages
on both sides?Yes.

08:56.361 --> 08:58.189
Everything you're about
to hear has been written

08:58.276 --> 09:01.671
by Beverly Goldberg
and sent to her children.

09:01.758 --> 09:03.107
This is all real.

09:03.194 --> 09:05.893
"Adam, I gave birth to you,
fed and nurtured you,

09:05.980 --> 09:08.635
"dried your tears,
and made you the center
of my universe.

09:08.722 --> 09:11.463
"But the way
you treated me today
makes me regret it all."

09:11.551 --> 09:13.335
Wait,
you really wrote this?

09:13.422 --> 09:16.207
Again, every word
is 100% true.

09:16.294 --> 09:18.862
"I don't know another
human being on this earth

09:18.949 --> 09:20.821
"who would treat
their parent this way,

09:20.908 --> 09:23.214
"especially four weeks
before Mother's Day."

09:23.301 --> 09:25.477
That's how you started
an actual letter?

09:25.565 --> 09:29.699
Oh, sweet,
stupid Vincent Geary.
The opening is everything.

09:29.786 --> 09:31.353
I call it the "guilt grabber."

09:31.440 --> 09:33.137
Oh, I got to
write this down.

09:33.224 --> 09:35.662
Wait. You can't just copy
what I say.

09:35.749 --> 09:37.315
Once I teach you
the basic structure,

09:37.402 --> 09:39.187
you have to find
your own spiteful voice.

09:39.274 --> 09:40.318
You have
a whole structure?

09:40.405 --> 09:41.581
Of course I do.

09:41.668 --> 09:44.540
Now,
after the guilt grabber,

09:44.627 --> 09:47.543
you deliver your
emotionally
devastating thesis,

09:47.630 --> 09:52.243
wherein you single them out
as the most ungrateful child
the world has ever known.

09:52.330 --> 09:55.333
"Not only am I ashamed to have
such a cruel, selfish son,

09:55.420 --> 09:58.467
"but I may never sleep again
knowing how I failed
as a mother."

09:58.554 --> 09:59.947
My God,
who writes this?

10:00.034 --> 10:02.123
Literally me, no joke.

10:02.210 --> 10:03.864
Next comes
the body of the letter,

10:03.951 --> 10:07.171
in which you present
the many hurtful specifics

10:07.258 --> 10:10.566
that demonstrate
how much you've sacrificed
for your baby.

10:10.653 --> 10:13.047
"I haven't slept
since you were born

10:13.134 --> 10:14.657
"and gave
my whole life to you.

10:14.744 --> 10:16.703
"Not once did I focus
on myself.

10:16.790 --> 10:18.182
"I could have been
a lawyer!"

10:18.269 --> 10:21.359
Again, something I actually
wrote to my children.

10:21.446 --> 10:23.623
Finally,
we have the closer,

10:23.710 --> 10:26.234
where you remind your children
that they, and they alone,

10:26.321 --> 10:28.453
are responsible
for your early demise.

10:28.540 --> 10:31.065
Wow.
I know, Serry Mirsky.

10:31.152 --> 10:33.458
You finally have the tool
to shame Emmy

10:33.545 --> 10:36.461
into being perfect
like class valedictorian
Aliza Goren.

10:36.548 --> 10:38.768
[LAUGHING]
She'll never be Aliza Goren.

10:38.855 --> 10:41.945
Beverly, these crazy guilt
letters are a game-changer.

10:42.032 --> 10:44.078
Thank you for this amazing,
hateful gift.

10:44.165 --> 10:46.167
You truly are
a genius of our time.

10:46.254 --> 10:48.299
It's so nice
to finally be recognized.

10:50.606 --> 10:51.999
Quick, give me your paper.
Let's not waste these.

10:54.001 --> 10:55.611
Your father
ruined my son.

10:55.698 --> 10:57.569
This morning,
Geoffrey said

10:57.657 --> 11:01.486
he wanted to go to a liberal
arts college like Vassar
where he can find himself.

11:01.573 --> 11:04.185
But you've mapped out
the next 10 years of his life,

11:04.272 --> 11:06.622
which ends in him taking over
your thriving practice.

11:06.709 --> 11:09.712
All I ever wanted was
an apprentice who cares,
but now there's no one.

11:09.799 --> 11:11.496
Geoff is as blind
as a patient

11:11.583 --> 11:13.411
who needs
a penetrating keratoplasty.

11:13.498 --> 11:16.066
I know. You rearranged
the entire filing system,

11:16.153 --> 11:18.503
and my apprentice wasn't
even here to see that.

11:18.590 --> 11:19.940
This is worse than
that one patient who had

11:20.027 --> 11:21.942
the viral eye infection
of the retina.

11:22.029 --> 11:23.595
Which I missed
and you pointed out.

11:23.683 --> 11:24.684
Thanks for that,
by the way.

11:24.771 --> 11:26.468
Enough is enough!

11:26.555 --> 11:28.905
You need an apprentice.
This is shameful.

11:28.992 --> 11:30.559
I want the old Geoff back!

11:30.646 --> 11:32.256
And you'll get him back!

11:32.343 --> 11:37.348
As leader of the JTP,
he has to do
exactly what I say.

11:37.435 --> 11:39.655
You will do
exactly what I say, Schwartz.

11:39.742 --> 11:40.830
No.
No?

11:40.917 --> 11:41.918
No.
No?

11:42.005 --> 11:43.354
Since when
does he say no?

11:43.441 --> 11:45.487
Since I'm done being
the doormat of the JTP.

11:45.574 --> 11:47.184
But that's your role.

11:47.271 --> 11:50.144
Each friendship group has
a doormat, a leader,

11:50.231 --> 11:52.973
a Naked One,
a tiny pocket man,
and a lame Matt Bradley!

11:53.060 --> 11:54.539
Well, I'm done
being the doormat.

11:56.454 --> 11:59.327
I hereby change the structure
of the JTP as we know it.

11:59.414 --> 12:01.068
You can't change that!

12:01.155 --> 12:02.460
It's the structure
of friendship!

12:02.547 --> 12:04.158
Oh, it's changed
but good.

12:04.245 --> 12:06.029
And as the new leader
of the JTP,

12:06.116 --> 12:07.727
I demand a piece
of your Gator Gum.

12:07.814 --> 12:09.729
There's only one man here
who needs Gatorade

12:09.816 --> 12:11.992
magically injected into
their gum and it's me.

12:12.079 --> 12:14.168
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS]

12:14.255 --> 12:17.171
Oh, dang. Geoff just swiped
some of Barry's Gator Gum.

12:17.258 --> 12:19.390
Oh, the Gator Gum
is totally replacing

12:19.477 --> 12:21.741
the vital salts and minerals
in Geoff's legs.

12:21.828 --> 12:26.180
No! Stop hydrating
with my Gator Gum!
Those are my electrolytes!

12:26.267 --> 12:28.791
Dude, he just quenched his
thirst with Barry's Gator Gum.
Geoff is our clear leader now.

12:28.878 --> 12:31.576
Damn right I am.
I'm so freakin' fired up
right now

12:31.663 --> 12:33.317
I'm gonna cut science class
and go run around the park.

12:33.404 --> 12:34.971
With no clear objective?

12:35.058 --> 12:36.538
That's crazy, dude.

12:36.625 --> 12:39.323
No. It's new Geoff.
JTP!

12:39.410 --> 12:40.585
ALL: JTP!

12:41.848 --> 12:43.501
New Geoff is exciting.

12:43.588 --> 12:45.852
Yeah, man.
That science lab was,
like, 30% of our grade,

12:45.939 --> 12:47.244
but new Geoff don't care.

12:47.331 --> 12:49.377
And this is an act of war.

12:49.464 --> 12:51.509
It's time I unleash
my sister.

12:51.596 --> 12:54.208
♪♪

12:54.295 --> 12:56.079
Hey, I wanted to...
Barry sent you, didn't he?

12:56.166 --> 12:58.516
Wow, yeah.
He charged into the kitchen
all sweaty and angry,

12:58.603 --> 13:00.170
and I said
I would come in here
just to get rid of him.

13:00.257 --> 13:01.998
Okay, well, why don't you
go tell Barry

13:02.085 --> 13:03.783
that new Geoff
is here to stay.

13:03.870 --> 13:05.828
Okay, I'm really not
in the loop, so what's
happening here?

13:05.915 --> 13:08.396
What's happening is the new me
refuses to be bossed around

13:08.483 --> 13:11.225
by his dad, his friends,
and quite frankly, you!

13:11.312 --> 13:13.140
Me? I'm part of this now?

13:13.227 --> 13:14.881
Yeah. I'm tired of folding
your sweaters.

13:14.968 --> 13:15.969
But I thought you liked
the folding.

13:16.056 --> 13:17.361
Does this answer
your question?

13:19.886 --> 13:22.627
♪♪

13:22.714 --> 13:23.759
No-go.
I like new Geoff.

13:23.846 --> 13:25.369
You like new Geoff?

13:25.456 --> 13:27.154
New Geoff is hot.
Good luck to you both.

13:27.241 --> 13:29.069
ADULT ADAM: As new Geoff
wasn't backing down,

13:29.156 --> 13:33.247
our bus full of kids and lame chaperones was pulling up to Hersheypark.

13:33.334 --> 13:35.684
Oh, you know what
those chocolate kiss
street lamps mean.

13:35.771 --> 13:37.425
We're here!

13:37.512 --> 13:40.297
It was a brutal start.
But once the bus parked,

13:40.384 --> 13:43.300
we were free to explore
Chocolate World
without our lame-ass par...

13:43.387 --> 13:45.389
Oh, balls!
They're back again!

13:45.476 --> 13:46.477
I don't get it.

13:46.564 --> 13:47.914
You all said you cut
your parents off

13:48.001 --> 13:49.306
from chaperoning
ages ago.

13:49.393 --> 13:51.613
I did, but last night
my mom wrote me

13:51.700 --> 13:54.007
this heartbreaking
eight-page letter,
and I caved.

13:54.094 --> 13:56.966
Same here. My dad even circled
his tears on the paper.

13:57.053 --> 13:58.620
My mom did
the same thing.

13:58.707 --> 14:00.056
Listen to this.

14:00.143 --> 14:02.624
"And when I literally die
from the disappointment,

14:02.711 --> 14:05.670
"please do not
visit my grave site.""...visit my grave site."

14:05.757 --> 14:06.454
Lemme see those letters.

14:07.411 --> 14:08.630
Look.

14:08.717 --> 14:10.284
They're all the same.

14:10.371 --> 14:13.200
See? My mom also has a hole
in her heart the shape of me.

14:13.287 --> 14:15.245
My mom has that same
kid-shaped hole!

14:15.332 --> 14:17.726
This can only be the work
of one woman...

14:17.813 --> 14:19.597
Beverly Goldberg.

14:19.684 --> 14:21.208
What are we gonna do,
man?

14:21.295 --> 14:22.905
I can't ever read
another one of these.

14:22.992 --> 14:25.255
I cried
in my mom's bosom.

14:25.342 --> 14:26.735
Her bosom!

14:26.822 --> 14:28.911
I'll tell you what
we're gonna do.

14:28.998 --> 14:32.175
We're gonna rise up
against this reign of guilt
and take back what is ours.

14:32.262 --> 14:35.048
Chocolatier!
We need chocolate-scented
stationery STAT!

14:35.135 --> 14:37.224
Time to give our parents
a taste of their own guilt.

14:38.225 --> 14:39.356
♪♪

14:39.443 --> 14:41.010
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

14:41.097 --> 14:44.884
All right, hit the showers or
generously spray on deodorant.

14:44.971 --> 14:47.625
Schwartz, got a bunch
of scoop balls that need
scooping, so have at it.

14:47.712 --> 14:49.845
Nah, man. I'm good.
Excuse me?

14:49.932 --> 14:51.238
I'm tired of being
Mr. Pushover

14:51.325 --> 14:53.153
who always scoops
the scoop balls after class.

14:53.240 --> 14:55.285
As leader of the JTP,
I say Andy does it.

14:55.372 --> 14:57.984
Hey! He's not the leader
of the JTP.

14:58.071 --> 14:58.898
You don't have to
do that, Andy.

14:58.985 --> 15:00.290
But Geoff said I should.

15:00.377 --> 15:02.031
Well, I say Geoff scoops
the scoop balls!

15:02.118 --> 15:03.119
You scoop
the scoop balls!

15:03.206 --> 15:04.555
I'm not scooping
no scoop balls!

15:04.642 --> 15:06.209
Somebody scoop
the scoop balls.

15:06.296 --> 15:07.515
I'll scoop the scoop balls,
okay?

15:07.602 --> 15:09.560
Don't you dare scoop
the scoop balls, Matthew!

15:09.647 --> 15:11.911
Fine! You'll all scoop
the scoop balls!

15:11.998 --> 15:15.131
Or better yet, [BLEEP],
why don't you scoop
my [BLEEP]?

15:15.740 --> 15:17.481
♪♪

15:17.568 --> 15:19.919
Never in all my years
in the gymanatorial arts

15:20.006 --> 15:22.095
have I ever been
so blatantly disrespected.

15:22.182 --> 15:24.358
I expected more from you,
Mr. Schwartz.

15:24.445 --> 15:26.099
Anything to say before
I decide your punishment?

15:26.186 --> 15:28.318
Yeah. Why am I here?

15:28.405 --> 15:30.712
The kid's got his own dad.
Call him.

15:30.799 --> 15:32.583
Yeah, but he's busy,
and he'll be so mad.

15:32.670 --> 15:34.455
But I'm busy
and I'm mad.

15:34.542 --> 15:36.413
You're mad? My jaw is
seizing up with anger.

15:36.500 --> 15:38.415
Dang it, Rick.
You got to chew some Gator Gum

15:38.502 --> 15:40.504
like a grown man
and calm the heck down.

15:40.591 --> 15:42.419
Follow me.
MURRAY: Oh, geez.

15:42.506 --> 15:44.334
What the hell's
wrong with you?

15:44.421 --> 15:46.946
Look, you're the one
who set me on this new path.

15:47.033 --> 15:49.644
We both agreed
I'm not involved
in any of this.

15:49.731 --> 15:52.168
Just saying you're
not involved doesn't
make you not involved.

15:52.255 --> 15:54.736
Look, I got my own
idiot kids to worry about.

15:54.823 --> 15:57.957
And you, you got a great dad
who wants you to be a doctor.

15:58.044 --> 16:00.046
You're the only one
who let me be me,

16:00.133 --> 16:01.656
and now even you're
taking it back.

16:01.743 --> 16:03.701
Thanks for nothing.

16:03.788 --> 16:06.269
♪♪

16:06.356 --> 16:09.055
ADULT ADAM: It was time
for us to take some
sweet revenge

16:09.142 --> 16:09.969
on our chaperone parents.

16:10.056 --> 16:12.536
Sup.
Sup yourselves.

16:12.623 --> 16:16.149
Uh, it is our job
as chaperones to
make sure you stay safe,

16:16.236 --> 16:18.455
and that extends
to sugar consumption.

16:18.542 --> 16:21.415
Then it's a good thing
we no longer accept you
as school chaperones.

16:21.502 --> 16:24.940
"Mother, I have clearly
failed as a son."

16:25.027 --> 16:26.942
What the hell is this?
It's a guilt letter,

16:27.029 --> 16:28.465
like the ones you taught
your friends to write.

16:28.552 --> 16:30.032
[GASPS] They know!
You know?

16:30.119 --> 16:31.860
We all know.
Chad Hayward Kremp, please.

16:31.947 --> 16:33.688
Think of me lying
in my grave site.

16:33.775 --> 16:35.603
That's my line.

16:35.690 --> 16:38.171
What she said,
but for me in my grave site.

16:38.258 --> 16:40.042
Sorry,
ladies and Vinny.

16:40.129 --> 16:42.697
This field/guilt trip
is over.

16:42.784 --> 16:44.481
We had an agreement.

16:44.568 --> 16:46.005
You were supposed to write
your own letters,

16:46.092 --> 16:47.615
but then you go
and copy mine?

16:47.702 --> 16:49.138
I tried to write my own,
Beverly.

16:49.225 --> 16:52.011
I just couldn't be a scathing
guilt monster like you.

16:52.098 --> 16:55.101
If you don't mind,
we're gonna head out
to Chocolate Town USA.

16:55.188 --> 16:57.146
Enjoy waiting
on the boiling hot bus.

16:57.233 --> 16:58.582
♪♪

16:58.669 --> 17:00.323
This is not the bus!

17:00.410 --> 17:02.456
I'm not riding my first
roller coaster with my mom!

17:02.543 --> 17:04.240
We need to talk
about your letter.

17:04.327 --> 17:07.113
My letter? You're the one
who's manipulated me
for years,

17:07.200 --> 17:08.636
and is that creaking
normal?

17:08.723 --> 17:10.464
That's because you were
shutting me out of your life,

17:10.551 --> 17:11.987
and, oh,
we keep climbing.

17:12.074 --> 17:14.033
Of course I shut you out!
I'm a teenager!

17:14.120 --> 17:15.730
And yeah, this is higher
than I thought.

17:15.817 --> 17:17.601
Here, hold my hand.
Let Mama protect you.

17:17.688 --> 17:19.908
Please, I'm gonna be
just fine!

17:19.995 --> 17:21.953
I'm gonna die, aah!

17:22.041 --> 17:23.999
Aah!

17:24.086 --> 17:28.003
I am so angry
and upside down!
Where's the ground?

17:28.090 --> 17:31.833
Aah, I was dead just now!
I'm so scared!

17:31.920 --> 17:34.009
Well, I'm loving
every moment of thi...

17:34.096 --> 17:37.708
Ohh! Help! We need
the coaster police!

17:37.795 --> 17:39.319
Where am I?

17:39.406 --> 17:40.842
Aah!

17:40.929 --> 17:43.323
I'm so furious
but I forget why!

17:43.410 --> 17:44.628
Aah!

17:44.715 --> 17:46.804
I'm blind!

17:46.891 --> 17:48.937
I am blind!

17:49.024 --> 17:50.460
[GASPS]

17:50.547 --> 17:52.332
So are we good?
Did we resolve this?

17:52.419 --> 17:54.116
Maybe! I don't know
anything anymore!

17:54.203 --> 17:57.337
Yes, I agree,
and I love you, too.

17:57.424 --> 17:59.078
ADULT ADAM: Yeah,
even though I blacked out
from terror,

17:59.165 --> 18:00.644
I was still super fired up.

18:00.731 --> 18:03.604
Adam, wait.

18:03.691 --> 18:06.302
I've given you four hours
of bus ride to cool off...

18:06.389 --> 18:08.348
Trust me, that's not
nearly enough.

18:08.435 --> 18:10.785
Okay, so maybe it was
a mistake for me

18:10.872 --> 18:11.960
to force my way
on this trip.

18:12.047 --> 18:13.918
Of course it was!

18:14.005 --> 18:17.661
My God, every other parent
was fine not to chaperone.
Why not you?

18:17.748 --> 18:21.578
Adam, when you were little,
I was your everything.

18:21.665 --> 18:26.583
I'd hold your hand when
I'd walk you into school,
and you'd cry when I left.

18:26.670 --> 18:28.716
Now when you walk through
that door in the morning,

18:28.803 --> 18:29.804
you're just gone.

18:31.414 --> 18:32.894
And when you come home,
I get nothing.

18:32.981 --> 18:34.809
Come on, I tell you stuff.

18:34.896 --> 18:38.117
Please.
At best I get a "muh."

18:38.204 --> 18:40.380
That's why
I write the letters,

18:40.467 --> 18:42.730
so I can hear more,
hear anything.

18:42.817 --> 18:46.037
Okay, then.
I promise to give you
more than a "muh"

18:46.125 --> 18:50.390
if you promise to stop
with your crazy mom
manifestos.

18:50.477 --> 18:52.566
Guess I could cut back
a little.

18:52.653 --> 18:56.744
With you... I still have
plenty of hurtful things
to say to Barry and Erica.

18:56.831 --> 19:00.356
ADULT ADAM: That day,
me and my mom were
finally seeing eye to eye,

19:00.443 --> 19:04.230
and my dad decided
to help someone
see things more clearly.

19:04.317 --> 19:06.623
If you're here for a
discounted eye exam,
forget it.

19:06.710 --> 19:08.016
Not today.

19:08.103 --> 19:10.061
I just thought
maybe we could talk.

19:10.149 --> 19:13.326
What's to talk about?
Geoff was in trouble
and called you, not me.

19:13.413 --> 19:15.241
Look, I'm far from
the kind of guy

19:15.328 --> 19:17.025
who should be giving
parenting advice,

19:17.112 --> 19:21.247
but I have learned
you can't plan
your kid's life for them.

19:21.334 --> 19:23.162
It's just always been
my dream

19:23.249 --> 19:25.164
for him to follow
in my footsteps.

19:25.251 --> 19:26.948
I get it,
but is it his dream?

19:27.905 --> 19:29.429
I guess not.

19:29.516 --> 19:32.127
For what it's worth, whatever
Geoff does with his life,

19:32.214 --> 19:34.695
I know he's gonna be
amazing at it.
He's a good egg.

19:34.782 --> 19:37.698
Tell you the truth,
your son's not so bad, either.

19:37.785 --> 19:39.178
Barry?

19:39.265 --> 19:41.876
You know, he's fantastic
with the patients.

19:41.963 --> 19:44.313
Kid's gonna be
a hell of a doctor.Maybe.

19:44.400 --> 19:46.054
♪♪

19:46.141 --> 19:47.577
But I don't want
to get involved.

19:47.664 --> 19:49.492
♪ She drives me crazy

19:49.579 --> 19:51.581
♪ Ooh, ooh

19:51.668 --> 19:54.671
I see you're back
to folding my sweaters.

19:54.758 --> 19:58.719
Yeah. The whole, uh,
new Geoff thing,
it's just not who I am.

19:58.806 --> 20:00.982
Look, you don't know
who you are, and that's okay,

20:01.069 --> 20:02.766
'cause I don't know
who I am, either.

20:02.853 --> 20:04.681
Come on, you've got it
all figured out.

20:04.768 --> 20:07.293
Dude, I have no idea
what I'll end up doing
with my life.

20:07.380 --> 20:09.469
All I can do
is follow my heart.

20:09.556 --> 20:11.862
And I love seeing you
finally doing the same.

20:11.949 --> 20:13.386
LOU: [CLEARS THROAT]
Sorry to interrupt.

20:13.473 --> 20:15.866
I just wanted a word
with Geoffrey.

20:15.953 --> 20:18.826
Look, Dad,
I don't want to hear about
how I let you down...

20:18.913 --> 20:20.871
It doesn't matter
what I think.

20:20.958 --> 20:22.308
It's your life,

20:22.395 --> 20:24.179
and I want it to be
whatever you want it to be.

20:25.572 --> 20:26.790
As long as
it's not furniture.

20:26.877 --> 20:27.878
Oh, God, no.

20:27.965 --> 20:28.923
♪ She drives me crazy

20:29.010 --> 20:30.925
♪ Ooh, ooh

20:31.012 --> 20:33.667
♪ Like no one else

20:33.754 --> 20:35.625
Boofaloo!
How was your day?

20:35.712 --> 20:37.323
Muh.

20:37.410 --> 20:41.283
♪ And I can't help myself

20:41.370 --> 20:44.330
Actually, it was really good.
You want to hear about it?

20:44.417 --> 20:46.419
♪ She drives me crazy ♪

20:46.506 --> 20:48.334
ADULT ADAM: When we're kids,

20:48.421 --> 20:51.250
it's natural to want
to shut your parents out,

20:51.337 --> 20:52.860
but once you start opening up,

20:52.947 --> 20:55.558
you realize
it can be pretty sweet.

20:55.645 --> 20:57.343
♪♪

21:00.563 --> 21:04.088
Bev, I have one of
your actual letters,

21:04.175 --> 21:05.960
and it's a smooth...

21:06.047 --> 21:08.267
[LAUGHING] 12 pages.

21:08.354 --> 21:10.965
Now, I know they've told me
they don't read the letters.

21:11.052 --> 21:14.185
I don't believe them,
because here's a letter
that's 20 years old,

21:14.273 --> 21:16.187
and my son Adam
still saved it.

21:16.275 --> 21:19.582
"Not only am I ashamed to have
such a cruel, selfish son,

21:19.669 --> 21:23.543
"but I may never sleep again
knowing how I have failed
as a mother."

21:23.630 --> 21:25.109
Well, a little guilt
doesn't hurt.

21:25.196 --> 21:26.459
What can I tell you?
